app.title: Supplementary Materials
app.p: The following are available online, Table S1: Information on sources of Boswellia samples, concentrations of pentacyclic triterpenic acids (PTA) in Boswellia extracts, and vouchers specimens were deposited in the Herbarium of the Botanical Garden, Institute of Systemic Botany and Ecology, Ulm University; Table S2: Fractionated extraction of sample # 1 ( B. sacra, Superior Hojari). Yields of extraction, concentrations of pentacyclic triterpenic acids (PTA), and toxicity to breast cancer cells MDA-MD-231 (72 h, n = 3).
